<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Getting Started on Capa</title><link>https://capa.rxcloud.group/en/docs/gettingstarted/</link><description>Recent content in Getting Started on Capa</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en</language><atom:link href="https://capa.rxcloud.group/en/docs/gettingstarted/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>Using Configuration API</title><link>https://capa.rxcloud.group/en/docs/gettingstarted/configuration-usage/</link><pubDate>Wed, 27 Oct 2021 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://capa.rxcloud.group/en/docs/gettingstarted/configuration-usage/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="introduction">Introduction&lt;/h2>
&lt;ol>
&lt;li>
&lt;p>The configuration capabilities provided by CapaConfigurationClient require concrete implementation classes to adapt to different platforms (by inheriting the &lt;a href="https://github.com/capa-cloud/capa-java/blob/master/sdk-spi/src/main/java/group/rxcloud/capa/spi/configstore/CapaConfigStoreSpi.java">CapaConfigStoreSpi&lt;/a> abstract class), such as the example &lt;a href="https://github.com/capa-cloud/capa-java/blob/master/sdk-spi-demo/src/main/java/group/rxcloud/capa/spi/demo/configstore/DemoCapaConfigStore.java">DemoCapaConfigStore&lt;/a>.&lt;/p>
&lt;/li>
&lt;li>
&lt;p>Loading of the concrete implementation class is achieved through the SPI mechanism. The specific configuration process is: add a capa-component-configuration.properties file under the project&amp;rsquo;s resources path.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>Add a new property key: &amp;ldquo;group.rxcloud.capa.component.configstore.CapaConfigStore&amp;rdquo; with value: &amp;ldquo;full path of the implementation class&amp;rdquo;; add a new property key: &amp;ldquo;CONFIGURATION_COMPONENT_STORE_NAME&amp;rdquo; with value: &amp;ldquo;config store name&amp;rdquo;. Example:&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Using RPC API</title><link>https://capa.rxcloud.group/en/docs/gettingstarted/rpc-usage/</link><pubDate>Fri, 15 Oct 2021 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://capa.rxcloud.group/en/docs/gettingstarted/rpc-usage/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="steps">Steps&lt;/h2>
&lt;p>&lt;a href="https://github.com/capa-cloud/capa-java/blob/master/examples/src/main/java/group/rxcloud/capa/examples/rpc/DemoRpcClient.java">Example&lt;/a>&lt;/p>
&lt;ol>
&lt;li>Build RPC Client&lt;/li>
&lt;/ol>
&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="background-color:#f8f8f8;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;">&lt;code class="language-java" data-lang="java">&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>&lt;span style="color:#000">CapaRpcClient&lt;/span>&lt;span style="color:#f8f8f8;text-decoration:underline"> &lt;/span>&lt;span style="color:#000">capaRpcClient&lt;/span>&lt;span style="color:#f8f8f8;text-decoration:underline"> &lt;/span>&lt;span style="color:#ce5c00;font-weight:bold">=&lt;/span>&lt;span style="color:#f8f8f8;text-decoration:underline"> &lt;/span>&lt;span style="color:#204a87;font-weight:bold">new&lt;/span>&lt;span style="color:#f8f8f8;text-decoration:underline"> &lt;/span>&lt;span style="color:#000">CapaRpcClientBuilder&lt;/span>&lt;span style="color:#000;font-weight:bold">().&lt;/span>&lt;span style="color:#c4a000">build&lt;/span>&lt;span style="color:#000;font-weight:bold">();&lt;/span>&lt;span style="color:#f8f8f8;text-decoration:underline">
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/div>&lt;ol start="2">
&lt;li>Invoke request&lt;/li>
&lt;/ol>
&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="background-color:#f8f8f8;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;">&lt;code class="language-java" data-lang="java">&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>&lt;span style="color:#000">Mono&lt;/span>&lt;span style="color:#ce5c00;font-weight:bold">&amp;lt;&lt;/span>&lt;span style="color:#204a87;font-weight:bold">byte&lt;/span>&lt;span style="color:#ce5c00;font-weight:bold">[]&amp;gt;&lt;/span>&lt;span style="color:#f8f8f8;text-decoration:underline"> &lt;/span>&lt;span style="color:#000">responseMono&lt;/span>&lt;span style="color:#f8f8f8;text-decoration:underline"> &lt;/span>&lt;span style="color:#ce5c00;font-weight:bold">=&lt;/span>&lt;span style="color:#f8f8f8;text-decoration:underline"> &lt;/span>&lt;span style="color:#000">capaRpcClient&lt;/span>&lt;span style="color:#000;font-weight:bold">.&lt;/span>&lt;span style="color:#c4a000">invokeMethod&lt;/span>&lt;span style="color:#000;font-weight:bold">(&lt;/span>&lt;span style="color:#000">SERVICE_APP_ID&lt;/span>&lt;span style="color:#000;font-weight:bold">,&lt;/span>&lt;span style="color:#f8f8f8;text-decoration:underline">
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>&lt;span style="color:#f8f8f8;text-decoration:underline"> &lt;/span>&lt;span style="color:#4e9a06">&amp;#34;hello&amp;#34;&lt;/span>&lt;span style="color:#000;font-weight:bold">,&lt;/span>&lt;span style="color:#f8f8f8;text-decoration:underline">
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>&lt;span style="color:#f8f8f8;text-decoration:underline"> &lt;/span>&lt;span style="color:#4e9a06">&amp;#34;hello&amp;#34;&lt;/span>&lt;span style="color:#000;font-weight:bold">,&lt;/span>&lt;span style="color:#f8f8f8;text-decoration:underline">
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>&lt;span style="color:#f8f8f8;text-decoration:underline"> &lt;/span>&lt;span style="color:#000">HttpExtension&lt;/span>&lt;span style="color:#000;font-weight:bold">.&lt;/span>&lt;span style="color:#c4a000">POST&lt;/span>&lt;span style="color:#000;font-weight:bold">,&lt;/span>&lt;span style="color:#f8f8f8;text-decoration:underline">
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>&lt;span style="color:#f8f8f8;text-decoration:underline"> &lt;/span>&lt;span style="color:#204a87;font-weight:bold">null&lt;/span>&lt;span style="color:#000;font-weight:bold">,&lt;/span>&lt;span style="color:#f8f8f8;text-decoration:underline">
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>&lt;span style="color:#f8f8f8;text-decoration:underline"> &lt;/span>&lt;span style="color:#000">TypeRef&lt;/span>&lt;span style="color:#000;font-weight:bold">.&lt;/span>&lt;span style="color:#c4a000">BYTE_ARRAY&lt;/span>&lt;span style="color:#000;font-weight:bold">);&lt;/span>&lt;span style="color:#f8f8f8;text-decoration:underline">
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/div>&lt;ol start="3">
&lt;li>Get invocation result&lt;/li>
&lt;/ol>
&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="background-color:#f8f8f8;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;">&lt;code class="language-java" data-lang="java">&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>&lt;span style="color:#204a87;font-weight:bold">byte&lt;/span>&lt;span style="color:#ce5c00;font-weight:bold">[]&lt;/span>&lt;span style="color:#f8f8f8;text-decoration:underline"> &lt;/span>&lt;span style="color:#000">response&lt;/span>&lt;span style="color:#f8f8f8;text-decoration:underline"> &lt;/span>&lt;span style="color:#ce5c00;font-weight:bold">=&lt;/span>&lt;span style="color:#f8f8f8;text-decoration:underline"> &lt;/span>&lt;span style="color:#000">responseMono&lt;/span>&lt;span style="color:#000;font-weight:bold">.&lt;/span>&lt;span style="color:#c4a000">block&lt;/span>&lt;span style="color:#000;font-weight:bold">();&lt;/span>&lt;span style="color:#f8f8f8;text-decoration:underline">
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/div>&lt;h2 id="explanation">Explanation&lt;/h2>
&lt;ol>
&lt;li>The RPC capabilities provided by CapaRpcClient require concrete implementation, as shown in the example &lt;a href="https://github.com/capa-cloud/capa-java/blob/master/examples/src/main/java/group/rxcloud/capa/examples/rpc/DemoRpcClient.java">DemoCapaHttp&lt;/a>.&lt;/li>
&lt;li>After implementing DemoCapaHttp, it needs to be configured in &lt;a href="https://github.com/capa-cloud/capa-java/blob/master/sdk-spi-demo/src/main/resources/capa-component-rpc.properties">capa-component-rpc.properties&lt;/a>, and loaded through the SPI mechanism.&lt;/li>
&lt;/ol></description></item></channel></rss>